import subprocess, sys, sys

def run_input(inp):
    p = subprocess.Popen([sys.executable, 'solution.py'], stdin=subprocess.PIPE, stdout=subprocess.PIPE, stderr=subprocess.PIPE, text=True)
    out, err = p.communicate(inp)
    return p.returncode, out, err

# Sample tests
tests = [
    ("2\n4 8\n", "5\n"),
    ("3\n51 44 63\n", "384\n"),
    ("8\n577752 258461 183221 889769 278633 577212 392309 326001\n", "20241214\n"),
]

all_ok = True
for inp, expected in tests:
    rc, out, err = run_input(inp)
    ok = (out == expected)
    print('INPUT:\n' + inp + 'EXPECTED:\n' + expected + 'GOT:\n' + out + ('OK' if ok else 'FAIL'))
    if err:
        print('STDERR:\n' + err)
    all_ok = all_ok and ok

print('ALL_OK:', all_ok)
